This paper deals with the representation of graphs in 3D space, specifically with visibility representations. This topic falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the study of planar graphs (cs.DM), their properties and representations, and the use of algorithms to construct such representations (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of bar 1-visibility representations, which is a specific type of visibility representation (cs.GR).
